Reading through both documents carefully — great project by the way! Let me break everything down for you.

What is a Model class?
Looking at your UML class diagram in the analysis report, model classes are just plain data containers — they hold the data/attributes of your entities. In your project:

src/model/
├── Product.java        → productId, categoryId, name, brand
├── Store.java          → storeId, name, chainName
├── StoreLocation.java  → storeId, latitude, longitude, address
├── StockItem.java      → stockItemId, productId, storeId, currentPrice, discountedPrice
├── Category.java       → categoryId, name
├── Campaign.java       → campaignId, stockItemId, discountRate, startDate, endDate
├── AvailabilityTag.java → stockItemId, level (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW)
├── BasketItem.java     → basketId, stockItemId, quantity
├── PriceHistory.java   → historyId, stockItemId, date, price
├── RouteResult.java    → routeId, totalDistance, storeCount, totalCost
└── RouteResultStore.java → routeId, storeId
They have no logic — just fields, constructors, getters/setters.

What are Repositories?
Repositories are classes that query/filter data. Since you have no database (just JSON), they act as in-memory search layers. For example:

src/repository/
├── ProductRepository.java     → findByName(), findByCategory()
├── StoreRepository.java       → findAll(), findById()
├── StockItemRepository.java   → findByProductId(), findByStoreId()
├── CampaignRepository.java    → findActive(), findByStockItem()
└── PriceHistoryRepository.java → findByStockItemId()
DataLoader.java fills these repositories from your JSON files, then your services call the repositories to get data.

Deadline 2 — April 18th: What's Required
From the project PDF, Prototype Development (D2) needs:

1. Data & Model Layer — JSON files loaded via DataLoader.java, model classes working

2. Core Business Logic (Services) — your existing:

CampaignService.java + DiscountCalculator.java
PricingService.java + BasketCalculator.java
RouteOptimizer.java
3. Presentation Layer (JavaFX UI) — all 5 screens working:

SearchScreen.java
ComparisonScreen.java
BasketScreen.java
PriceHistoryScreen.java
MapRouteScreen.java
4. Prototype Testing & Integration — JUnit tests + all branches merged

⚠️ Important Note
The report says "prototype does NOT have to include full business logic" — focus is on the UI being functional and navigable. But your services should at least load and display real data from the JSONs.

